      "sampleOutput": "**Affiliate Partnership Strategy: Holistic Wellness for Busy Moms**\n\n**Program:** \"Holistic Wellness for Busy Moms\" (6-week coaching program)\n**Target Audience:** Busy mothers, aged 28-45, seeking stress reduction, better nutrition, and self-care strategies.\n\n**I. Ideal Affiliate Partner Profile:**\n\n*   **Type 1: Complementary Service Providers:** Nutritionists, personal trainers, doulas, lactation consultants, sleep coaches, therapists specializing in maternal mental health.\n*   **Type 2: Content Creators:** Mommy bloggers, parenting podcasters, influencers in wellness/parenting niches, YouTube channels focused on mom life.\n*   **Type 3: Related Products:** Brands selling organic baby food, meal prep services, ethical fashion for moms, wellness apps, self-care product boxes.\n*   **Key Traits:** Established audience of busy moms, high engagement, strong reputation, alignment with holistic wellness values, active online presence.\n\n**II. Affiliate Commission Structure:**\n\n*   **Standard Commission:** 20-30% of program sale for each successful referral.\n*   **Tiered Commission:** Increase commission percentage after a certain number of sales (e.g., 5 sales = 25%, 10 sales = 30%).\n*   **Bonus Incentives:** Occasional bonuses for top performers or during launch periods (e.g., extra $50 for every 3 sales in a month).\n*   **Cookie Duration:** 60-90 days to ensure partners get credit for delayed purchases.\n\n**III. Outreach & Recruitment Strategy:**\n\n*   **Discovery:** Research potential partners via social media, Google search (e.g., \"best mommy blogs 2024\"), industry events, and competitor analysis.\n*   **Personalized Outreach:** Craft tailored emails or DMs highlighting mutual benefits and audience synergy. Focus on how the partnership serves *their* audience.\n*   **Affiliate Portal:** Set up a dedicated page on your website with program details, FAQs for affiliates, and an application form.\n*   **Networking:** Attend parenting or wellness industry conferences and events to meet potential partners in person.\n\n**IV. Affiliate Support & Resources:**\n\n*   **Welcome Kit:** Comprehensive guide on your program, ideal client, and how to talk about it.\n*   **Marketing Assets:** Pre-written email swipes, social media graphics/templates, banner ads, unique tracking links.\n*   **Content Collaboration Ideas:** Offer to guest post on their blog, be interviewed on their podcast, or provide exclusive content for their audience.\n*   **Regular Communication:** Monthly newsletters with program updates, success tips, and promotional ideas.\n*   **Dedicated Support:** A point person for affiliate questions.\n\n**V. Tracking & Payouts:**\n\n*   **Affiliate Software:** Utilize a reliable platform (e.g., Thrivecart, Kartra, ClickFunnels, LeadDyno) to manage links, track sales, and handle payouts.\n*   **Payout Schedule:** Monthly or quarterly payouts via PayPal or bank transfer.\n*   **Transparency:** Provide affiliates with a dashboard to track their own sales and commissions.\n\n**VI. Legal & Compliance:**\n\n*   **Affiliate Agreement:** Clear terms and conditions outlining commission, payout schedule, forbidden promotional tactics, and legal compliance (e.g., FTC disclosure requirements).\n*   **Disclosure:** Educate affiliates on the importance of disclosing their affiliate relationship to their audience.",
